Colombia Stocks: Bancolombia Declines; Textiles Fabricato Rises

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-04-08T16:45:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/colombia-stocks-bancolombia-declines-textiles-fabricato-rises.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:30 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.6 percent to 14,588.40, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.6 percent to 1,713.18.  Bancolombia SA (PFBCOLO)   fell 1.8 percent to 29,380
pesos. Standpoint Research lowered the recommendation on
Bancolombia’s American depositary receipts to “hold” from
“accumulate,” according to a report e-mailed today.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)   rose 1.1
percent to 44.8 pesos. An agreement on labor-rights issues with
 Colombia  will help advance a stalled free trade agreement, U.S.
President  Barack Obama  said late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  